  Aug. 20, 2025, at 12:00 p.m.
  
  SaveAdd us on
  
  _More_
  
  [![U.S. News & World Report](https://www.usnews.com/static/img/usn-logo-large.svg)](https://www.usnews.com/)
  
  The Best Glamping Resorts in the U.S.
  
  _More_
  
  ![Exterior of illuminated glamping tents at BaseCamp 37 at night.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000198-c2a1-dd48-a19b-e7f1566a0000/main-image-credit-basecamp-37.jpg?update-time=1755612009854&size=responsive640)
  
  Courtesy of BaseCamp 37
  
  If you're enticed by the idea of camping but don't want to deal with the inevitable grunt work that comes with it, glamping (or glamorous camping) is the perfect compromise. With access to unique facilities, luxurious amenities and standout service – along with the ability to sustainably connect to nature – it's no wonder that glamping is on the rise. Read on to discover the most unique glamping resorts in California, Utah, Tennessee and other destinations across the U.S.
  
  ## **Paws Up Montana: Greenough, Montana**
  
  ![Exterior shot of snowy cabin at Paws Up Montana.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-24f2-dc34-a9f3-a7fe66d70000/3-exterior-the-resort-at-paws-up.jpg?update-time=1755620924838&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Paws Up Montana
  
  There's glamping, and then there's glamping at [Paws Up Montana](https://travel.usnews.com/hotels/review-The_Resort_at_Paws_Up-Greenough-US-150160/). One of the pioneers of modern-day glamping, Paws Up Montana features six exclusive glamping camps (with prices to match), each one offering a different experience. Solo travelers and couples will love the secluded two-story Tree Haus at the resort's adults-only retreat, called the green o. North Bank Camp – with two- and three-bedroom tents – is ideal for large families. You can book an individual tent or, if traveling with extended family or friends, even an entire camp. Guests can also bring along a furry friend, as this resort is dog-friendly.
  
  Glamping guests enjoy a dedicated camping butler and, because this is an [all-inclusive resort](https://travel.usnews.com/gallery/the-top-all-inclusive-resorts-in-the-usa), three gourmet meals with alcoholic and nonalcoholic beverages daily. Select activities such as mountain biking, broom hockey and archery are covered in nightly rates. For additional fees, you can also take advantage of the many unique guided activities and excursions you don't find at most resorts, from snowmobiling to hot air balloon rides. On-site transportation and shuttle service to and from Missoula Montana Airport, about 35 miles away, are also included in your stay.
  
  While the lodging and amenities make Paws Up one of the best glamping resorts in the U.S., it's the staff members who have earned this resort rave reviews from previous guests. Paws Up Montana offers glamping mid-May through mid-October, while the green o is available for stays year-round.
  
  Address: [40060 Paws Up Road, Greenough, MT 59823](https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Resort+at+Paws+Up/@46.916983,-113.4373509,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x535dab4a7c82b58d:0xea52da2857ff3070!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d46.9169794!4d-113.434776!16s%2Fg%2F1tt8byls?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Terramor Outdoor Resort: Bar Harbor, Maine
  
  ![Interior of tent with two chairs in front of a bed at Terramor Outdoor Resort.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-24f2-dc34-a9f3-a7fe671a0000/4-interior-terramor-outdoor-resort.jpg?update-time=1755620962999&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Terramor Outdoor Resort
  
  Terramor Outdoor Resort offers luxury tent accommodations near [Acadia National Park](https://travel.usnews.com/Acadia_National_Park_ME/Things_To_Do/) in Maine. All tents feature electricity, Wi-Fi, portable heaters and coolers, plus other convenient perks; though, the types vary in capacity from two up to five guests and whether they have a bathroom. This family-friendly resort features an abundance of amenities that travelers love, including a pool and hot tub, lawn games, live entertainment, evening campfires, stargazing lectures, and an on-site restaurant and bar where guests can enjoy craft cocktails and regionally sourced beers. Pets are also welcome at Terramor, especially in the on-site dog park.
  
  Terramor is a designated stop for the Island Explorer, a free shuttle service that transports visitors to Acadia National Park, downtown [Bar Harbor](https://travel.usnews.com/Bar_Harbor_ME/Things_To_Do/) and other areas of interest on Mount Desert Island. The Island Explorer operates seasonally, from mid-June to mid-October.
  
  Address: [1453 Maine state Route 102, Bar Harbor, ME 04609](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Terramor+Outdoor+Resort/@44.4047111,-68.3444118,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x4cae9548a6bed1a5:0x61ec395cc118e694!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d44.4047073!4d-68.3418369!16s%2Fg%2F11j11bntw3?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Backland: Williams, Arizona
  
  ![Interior of cabin room with a bed facing a large window at Backland.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-24f2-dc34-a9f3-a7fe666e0000/5-interior-backland.jpg?update-time=1755620998377&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Backland
  
  Backland is a remote resort with two glamping options: Backland Suites and Sky Suites. The latter features a 16-foot skylight over the bed for stargazing, but both options are fitted with panoramic windows for breathtaking views of the Arizona wilderness. These luxury tents accommodate up to either four or six guests, plus no more than two pets. Each tent includes a king-size bed, a full en suite bathroom with a shower, luxury linens, electricity, automatic climate control, an outdoor patio and more.
  
  Backland doesn't offer Wi-Fi in the tents – only at reception – as guests are encouraged to unplug during their stays. Instead of doomscrolling on social media, you can enjoy bird-watching, stargazing, Frisbee golf and roasting s'mores over a campfire. There's also on-site dining, as well as a pond with a beach and complimentary kayaks. Glampers at this resort say they appreciate the cozy accommodations and peaceful atmosphere.
  
  Backland is located less than 15 miles from downtown Williams, Arizona, close to some of the [best places to visit in Arizona](https://travel.usnews.com/rankings/best-places-to-visit-in-arizona/), including [Flagstaff](https://travel.usnews.com/Flagstaff_AZ/Things_To_Do/) (about 40 miles away), [Grand Canyon National Park](https://travel.usnews.com/Grand_Canyon_AZ/Things_To_Do/) (less than 70 miles) and [Sedona](https://travel.usnews.com/Sedona_AZ/Things_To_Do/), which is a roughly 65-mile drive from the resort.
  
  Address: [6929 E. Rosilda Springs Road, Williams, AZ 86046](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Backland+Glamping+Resort/@35.176384,-112.0529722,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x872d63c03714deeb:0xd6d57330b70cb12c!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d35.1763796!4d-112.0503973!16s%2Fg%2F11t9kw_lrw?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Klarhet: Lutsen, Minnesota
  
  ![Exterior shot of dome windowed tent at Klarhet.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-2517-dba3-abd7-273f35840000/klarhet.jpeg?update-time=1755621018741&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Klarhet
  
  Klarhet, which means "clarity" in Swedish, aims to bring just that to its glamping guests. The intimate property is located on the shores of Lake Superior and surrounded by a regenerative food forest, where an assortment of animals and edible plants attempts to mimic natural ecosystems – and where guests are invited to experience the lakefront through tours, tastings and more.
  
  Klarhet offers four domes – Raidho, Dagaz, Laguz and Berkanan – which all use large panels to showcase stellar views of the night sky and lush greenery. Domes come equipped with king- or queen-size beds, sustainably sourced cotton bedding, Turkish bathrobes and custom rainfall showers. Activities at Klarhet include meeting the property's goat herd and cozying up around the communal fire pit. Recent guests praise everything about Klarhet, from the accommodations to the staff.
  
  Address: [233 Ski Hill Road, Lutsen, MN 55612](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Klarhet/@47.6490283,-90.7110259,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x52a633a40c9efdbb:0xcd5ddf93e43d526b!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d47.6490247!4d-90.708451!16s%2Fg%2F11s0xmc43b?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Bodhi Farms: Bozeman, Montana
  
  ![Exterior shot of tent in grassy field at Bodhi Farms.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-2517-dba3-abd7-273f360c0000/11-exterior-bodhi-farms.jpeg?update-time=1755621040027&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Bodhi Farms
  
  Nestled beside the Gallatin Mountains, Bodhi Farms allows travelers to sustainably and authentically experience the beauty of Montana through immersive activities and amenities. The warmer months boast yoga and spa services along the creek, farming experiences such as gardening and culinary classes, a wood-fired sauna, nightly campfires, and fly fishing both on- and off-site. Farm-to-table dining at the field kitchen restaurant, situated on an open-air Creekside pavilion during the summer, includes the opportunity to try the Cowboy Brunch. Complimentary breakfast is available to guests of the hotel's nine glamping tents, another highlight of this [eco-resort](https://travel.usnews.com/gallery/top-ecolodges-around-the-world).
  
  Available for stays from May to October, each cone-shaped tent features either one king-size bed or two twin beds, plus plush pet beds for up to two dogs. The accommodations let in plenty of natural light and come equipped with a private porch and a hammock, plus extra heaters and fans upon request. Luxurious bathrooms are shared yet still feel private, and Bodhi Farms provides natural toiletries and complimentary bathrobes.
  
  Less than 15 miles south of Bozeman, Montana, Bodhi Farms' location makes a convenient base to visit some of the [state's top attractions](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-things-to-do-in-montana), including Big Sky Resort and [Yellowstone National Park](https://travel.usnews.com/Yellowstone_National_Park_WY/Things_To_Do/), one of the top-rated [national parks in the U.S.](https://travel.usnews.com/rankings/best-national-parks-in-the-usa/)
  
  Address: [13624 S. Cottonwood Road, Bozeman, MT 59718](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Bodhi+Farms/@45.5717968,-111.1361272,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x5345517993156bef:0x6b920afd111c91b9!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d45.5717931!4d-111.1335523!16s%2Fg%2F11h5616xk0?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Camp Long Creek: Ridgedale, Missouri
  
  ![Exterior shot of a bright tent at Camp Long Creek in the evening.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-2517-dba3-abd7-273f36450000/12-wide-shote-camp-long-creek.jpg?update-time=1755621060817&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Camp Long Creek
  
  Named for its location on Table Rock Lake at [Big Cedar Lodge](https://travel.usnews.com/hotels/review-Big_Cedar_Lodge-Ridgedale-Missouri-114070/) (created by the founder of Bass Pro Shops), Camp Long Creek offers glamping near [Branson, Missouri](https://travel.usnews.com/Branson_MO/Things_To_Do/). Its glamping units bring wood floors and chandeliers into a canvas tent, with each offering an outdoor bathtub, a fire pit, a table and chairs, a small fridge and coffee maker, and sleeping accommodations for two. These tents are scattered around the property, so views range from the lake to the forest. All units are dog-friendly and feature a private bathroom.
  
  When you're not white-knuckling the roller coasters at Silver Dollar City (considered one of the [best amusement parks in the U.S.](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-amusement-parks-in-the-us)) or uncovering history at the [Titanic Museum](https://travel.usnews.com/Branson_MO/Things_To_Do/Titanic_Museum_63378/), take time to enjoy the resort's activities, such as golfing, hiking, or boating and fishing on the lake. Other amenities include an infinity pool and a bocce ball court. Previous guests rave about the setting and conveniences of glamping at this resort.
  
  Address: [1358 Long Creek Road, Ridgedale, MO 65739](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Camp+Long+Creek/@36.5207332,-93.3050228,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x87cee3ad3ad3afd5:0x77db86722cf81931!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d36.5207289!4d-93.3024479!16s%2Fg%2F1tl9n2y1?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Alila Ventana Big Sur: Big Sur, California
  
  ![Interior of Wildwood glamping tent at Alila Ventana Big Sur.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2b00a0000/2-ventana-big-sur.jpg?update-time=1755621115679&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Alila Ventana Big Sur
  
  Few [destinations in California](https://travel.usnews.com/rankings/best-places-to-visit-in-california/) offer luxury in a place where you would otherwise have to rough it. In [Big Sur](https://travel.usnews.com/Big_Sur_CA/Things_To_Do/), a region that is only accessible via one road and doesn't always offer electricity, travelers will find a limited selection of five-star accommodations, among them [Alila Ventana Big Sur](https://travel.usnews.com/Hotels/review-Ventana_Inn_Spa-Big_Sur-California-112228/).
  
  The resort offers safari-style tents in a 40-acre redwood canyon, all equipped with plush beds, electric lamps, instant hot and cold potable water via sinks, and power outlets with charging ports. Glampers can also make use of amenities for enjoying the outdoors, such as Adirondack chairs, wood-burning fire pits and picnic tables. The campgrounds are dog-friendly. Restrooms and showers are available at a shared, well-maintained bathhouse.
  
  While all guests are welcome at the on-site Sur House Restaurant, some property amenities like the swimming pools and fitness studios are reserved for resort guests only. There are a limited number of resort passes for glampers available, so make sure to reserve yours in advance.
  
  Address: [48123 California state Route 1, Big Sur, CA 93920](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Alila+Ventana+Big+Sur/@36.2291713,-121.7629286,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x808d8456bb4936e1:0xabe1434825b2ed03!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d36.229167!4d-121.7603537!16s%2Fg%2F1hdz67rfm?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Treebones Resort: Big Sur, California
  
  ![Exterior shot of Treebones Resort overlooking the ocean.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-24f9-dc34-a9f3-a7ff31cc0000/treebones-resort2-credit-kodiak-greenwood.jpg?update-time=1755621136143&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Kodiak Greenwood
  
  You might also consider Treebones Resort if you want to glamp in Big Sur, which features yurts with king-size beds and modern furnishings, as well as accommodations you're not likely to find elsewhere. The Autonomous Camp Collection's twin units, which can best be described as a full apartment fit into a tent, take glamping to the next level; this solar-powered, upscale option is complete with a bedroom, en suite bathroom, lounge area and outdoor deck with ocean views. For a more rustic but no less unique stay, the Human Nest campsite is a futon pad inside a collection of large, woven sticks and branches. The nest is not fully covered or insulated, so you'll need to bring your own bedding and tent in case of surprise wind and rain. The handwoven Twig Hut is a similar, more traditional option for those wanting a less extreme outdoor option.
  
  Something else Treebones Resort has that you don't find at most glamping resorts: sushi. The Wild Coast Sushi Bar features an omakase dining experience in which patrons sit face-to-face with the chef as they craft the 15-course tasting menu. Previous guests say it's an absolute must when staying here. You can also dine at The Lodge Restaurant, which serves a complimentary breakfast buffet and offers lunch and a four-course dinner.
  
  Other on-site amenities include a massage studio and yoga. The rugged coastline views at Treebones Resort rival many in the area, and glampers may also choose to explore the beauty of Big Sur through guided excursions.
  
  Address: [71895 California state Route 1, Big Sur, CA 93920](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Treebones+Resort/@35.8842571,-121.4578777,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x8092a2af99d70411:0xa00c55b3640bdc08!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d35.8842528!4d-121.4553028!16s%2Fg%2F1tqclg81?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Under Canvas: Multiple Locations
  
  ![Interior of camping tent with large bed at an Under Canvas location.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2b5930000/3-ucmoabcredit-baileymade20.jpg?update-time=1755621183132&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Bailey Made\|Courtesy of Under Canvas
  
  First-time glampers should consider Under Canvas, which offers more than a dozen glamping locations nationwide, including [Zion National Park](https://travel.usnews.com/Zion_National_Park_UT/Things_To_Do/), the Great Smoky Mountains, the [Grand Canyon](https://travel.usnews.com/Grand_Canyon_AZ/Things_To_Do/) and Acadia National Park.
  
  Under Canvas offers multiple different options of safari-style tents (which vary by location) to accommodate solo travelers, couples and families. Guests in the Suite, Stargazer and Deluxe tents enjoy king-size beds, wood-burning stoves, West Elm patio furnishings, and en suite bathrooms with organic bath products and hot running water. On-site cafe-style dining (including locally sourced ingredients) is available in addition to complimentary camp programming that spans yoga, guided hikes, live acoustic music, fireside chats and s'mores. Other amenities vary by location.
  
  Under Canvas operates seasonally, with dates varying for each site.
  
  ## ULUM Moab: Moab, Utah
  
  ![Interior of spacious glamping tent at ULUM Moab.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000189-98c3-d382-a9ff-99ffcd6a0000/ulum-moab-credit-bailey-made.jpg?update-time=1755621211936&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Bailey Made
  
  An elevated experience by Under Canvas, ULUM caters to travelers in search of the ultimate luxury-meets-camping experience. As such, all Suite Tents feature a plush king-size bed with Parachute linens; a living area with a queen-size bed and chairs; an en suite bathroom with a rain shower, Aesop toiletries and Turkish cotton bathrobes; a wood-burning stove; and a private deck. All accommodations are dog-friendly.
  
  ULUM Moab also offers on-site dining, three dipping pools, a yoga deck, sound bath meditation and more. You can even book a guided adventure such as stargazing in Moab, rafting the Colorado River, or hiking in [Arches](https://travel.usnews.com/Arches_National_Park_UT/Things_To_Do/) or Canyonlands national parks. Reviews of the resort are strongly positive, with many mentioning the location and staff among their favorite highlights.
  
  Address: [147 Looking Glass Road, Moab, Utah 84503](https://www.google.com/maps/place/ULUM+Moab/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x87380430969c955f:0x72a31982f42b8c86?sa=X&ved=1t:242&ictx=111)
  
  ## Little Arrow Outdoor Resort: Townsend, Tennessee
  
  ![Exterior shot of misty cabin with a woman on the porch at Little Arrow Outdoor Resort.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-24f9-dc34-a9f3-a7ff31900001/little-arrow-outdoor-resort.png?update-time=1755621253497&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Little Arrow Outdoor Resort
  
  Aside from Under Canvas' Great Smoky Mountains location, there are several individually owned resorts and rentals with glamping in [Tennessee](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-things-to-do-in-tennessee). Among the best options is Little Arrow Outdoor Resort, which offers glamping tents in addition to its modernized cabins and tiny homes.
  
  These glamping accommodations come in three forms: the Luxury Glamping Lodge, Luxury Glamping Tents and Primitive Glamping Tents. All are equipped with plush bedding, heating and air conditioning, and a fire pit with a grill grate. The luxury options come with private bathrooms and kitchenettes, while the "primitive" experience means you'll have to venture over to the bathhouses.
  
  Resort amenities include a lounge with coffee, games and books; a zero-entry swimming pool, splash pad and hot tub; a dog park (yes, the resort is pet-friendly); a community garden; sports courts; and more. Don't forget to explore [Great Smoky Mountains National Park](https://travel.usnews.com/Great_Smoky_Mountains_National_Park_TN/Things_To_Do/), just minutes from the resort. Recent guests say Little Arrow Outdoor Resort is especially fun for families and groups.
  
  Address: [118 Stables Drive, Townsend, TN 37882](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Little+Arrow+Outdoor+Resort/@35.6707411,-83.7184398,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x885ea92958cd6929:0xd66cf5d3dfd62694!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d35.6707368!4d-83.7158649!16s%2Fg%2F1tnmsf_z?entry=ttu)
  
  ## **Collective Governors Island: Governors Island, New York**
  
  ![Interior of glamping tent with Southwestern accents at Collective Governors Island.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2d2c00000/7-courtesy-of-collective-retreats.jpg?update-time=1755621303582&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Collective Retreats
  
  Did you know you can go glamping in [New York City](https://travel.usnews.com/New_York_NY/Things_To_Do/)? Collective Retreats, which manages the Conservatory Collective (a group of outdoor and nature retreats around the world), operates a location on Governors Island just an 8-minute ferry ride from the city.
  
  You'll find 29 tents and cabins across the property, with each site boasting a private deck and green space. While some tent types, such as the Voyager King Tent, feature an en suite bathroom, others require you to use a shared bathhouse. Breakfast, ferry transportation and evening campfire s'mores are included in the nightly rates.
  
  Enjoy farm-to-island fare at Three Peaks Lodge, or light bites and sips at Sunset Terrace Bar. You'll find plenty of experiences and activities to enjoy, such as biking around Governors Island and playing lawn games in the property's large meadow.
  
  Address: [825 Gresham Road, New York, NY 10004](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Collective+Retreats+Governors+Island/@40.6889253,-74.0215567,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x89c25ba283e6ea09:0x27f0852e5c1c924d!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d40.6889253!4d-74.0215567!16s%2Fg%2F11gh_p3pgn?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDgxMy4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D)
  
  ## Capitol Reef Resort: Torrey, Utah
  
  ![Conestoga wagons and Adirondack checks around a fire at Capitol Reef Resort.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2e09e0000/8-capitol-reef-resort.jpg?update-time=1755621369062&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Capitol Reef Resort
  
  Capitol Reef Resort is among several places in the U.S. where glamping takes the form of a Conestoga wagon. The resort's Conestoga wagons can sleep up to six guests thanks to two twin bunk beds accompanying the king-size bed. They feature lighting, Wi-Fi, air conditioning and beautiful rustic furnishings. Additionally, guests have access to detached private bathrooms located a short distance away.
  
  The resort also gives lodgers the option to stay in conical glamping tents, which sleep two adults and come with much of the same amenities as the wagons – plus flat-screen TVs. Both glamping options are available seasonally, typically from May to October.
  
  Capitol Reef Resort offers on-site dining and a seasonal outdoor pool and year-round hot tub with views of Utah's red rock cliffs. Previous guests say it's a convenient place to stay if you plan to explore Capitol Reef National Park, one of the lesser-known [treasures in Utah](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-things-to-do-in-utah).
  
  Address: [2600 Utah state Route 24, Torrey, UT 84775](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Capitol+Reef+Resort/@38.3201122,-111.3851399,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x874a15877a0f80f1:0x29a5ca0e282ca87e!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d38.320108!4d-111.382565!16s%2Fg%2F1tffzzvx?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Sinya on Lone Man Creek: Wimberley, Texas
  
  ![Outdoor tub on a porch at Sinya on Lone Man Creek.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2e31f0000/9-sinya.jpg?update-time=1755621404412&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Sinya on Lone Man Creek
  
  Experience the beauty – and the [award-winning wineries](https://travel.usnews.com/gallery/top-texas-wineries-to-visit) – of Texas Hill Country at Sinya on Lone Man Creek, a property inspired by a trip to Tanzania and named after a baby elephant in Kenya. This [top Texas glamping retreat](https://travel.usnews.com/features/glamping-in-texas-the-best-resorts) is situated atop a ridge, making you feel as if you're in a treehouse overlooking the beautiful surrounding greenery and Lone Man Creek. The creek's name aptly sets the scene for this exclusive experience, since the property consists of only one tent. The tent can accommodate two guests, so there's no need to be truly "alone" if you don't wish to be.
  
  This singular tent is decked out in beautiful country-style furnishings and outfitted with a king-size bed (not to mention goose-down pillows), a Nespresso coffee maker, a feather-cushioned sofa, a kitchenette and a bathroom, which features a claw-foot tub, bathrobes and Turkish towels. Venture outside and you'll find the resort has five furnished outdoor spaces for lounging, including a deck with a hot tub and shower. Recent guests, many of whom visited with a romantic partner, appreciate the seclusion of this glamping resort.
  
  Address: [428 Deer Lake Estates, Wimberley, TX 78676](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Sinya+On+Lone+Man+Creek/@30.0305178,-98.0501802,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x865b5dfde7183107:0x20d030601a6381e2!8m2!3d30.0305132!4d-98.0476053!16s%2Fg%2F11stnj8g0v?entry=ttu)
  
  Read:
  
  [19 Most Romantic Getaways in Texas](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-romantic-getaways-in-texas)
  
  ## The Ranch at Rock Creek: Philipsburg, Montana
  
  ![Interior of glamping tent with twin beds at The Ranch at Rock Creek.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2e8530000/10-the-ranch-at-rock-creeek.jpg?update-time=1755621440239&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of The Ranch at Rock Creek
  
  This five-star dude ranch in western Montana, frequently lauded for providing one-of-a-kind travel experiences, also specializes in glamping. Like the rest of its property and offerings, [The Ranch at Rock Creek](https://travel.usnews.com/Hotels/review-The_Ranch_at_Rock_Creek-Philipsburg-Montana-150315/) takes its glamping to the next level.
  
  Glamping accommodations include part-tent, part-cabin dwellings in four styles, ranging from 630 square feet to 1,300 square feet. Amenities vary inside these "canvas cabins," but you'll typically find spacious bedrooms, additional living areas, gas stoves, attached bathrooms, and outdoor spaces such as porches or decks. The Trapper and Sweet Grass cabins are open year-round, and the Trapper Cabin allows pets. Guests can also add a 180-square-foot covered Conestoga wagon, which has a king-size bed and twin bunks, to their stay from mid-May through Labor Day.
  
  What's more, glamping accommodations qualify for the resort's all-inclusive rate, which covers farm-to-table meals, drinks, transportation on the ranch and some airport transfers, as well as resort activities like horseback riding and archery. Peak season at this property spans late May to early September, but the property is open year-round. The Ranch at Rock Creek exceeds expectations, according to previous guests.
  
  Address: [79 Carriage House Lane, Philipsburg, MT 59858](https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Ranch+at+Rock+Creek/@46.2564277,-113.5247059,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x535c751df9da3d3b:0x816e62d5843db70e!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d46.256424!4d-113.522131!16s%2Fg%2F1tfk8pgc?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Borealis Basecamp: Fairbanks, Alaska
  
  ![Aerial view of domed glamping tent at Borealis Basecamp.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9181-d679-ad7f-b1e19b530000/200727glampingresorts-submitted.jpg?update-time=1755621481366&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Borealis Basecamp
  
  If you've ever dreamed of sleeping beneath [the northern lights in Alaska](https://travel.usnews.com/features/northern-lights-in-alaska), it's time to plan a stay at Borealis Basecamp. Located less than 30 miles north of [Fairbanks](https://travel.usnews.com/Fairbanks_AK/Things_To_Do/), Borealis Basecamp unfurls across 100 acres and offers igloos and cubes in lieu of tents, further elevating the one-of-a-kind experience.
  
  These fiberglass igloos feature cozy beds, Wi-Fi access, private bathrooms with showers and hairdryers, free toiletries and hot beverages, and a 16-foot windowed ceiling so guests can fall asleep admiring the aurora borealis when it's visible. The cube accommodations feature most of the same amenities, but instead of skylights, guests enjoy floor-to-ceiling windows and "treehouse" beds with viewing windows just for kids, plus an en suite bathroom. Not surprisingly, recent guests say staying at Borealis Basecamp was one of the most unique experiences they've ever had.
  
  Address: [2640 Himalaya Road, Fairbanks, AK 99712](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Borealis+Basecamp/@65.1028769,-147.8867301,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x513214dbb0d47305:0x264242833a907f76!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d65.1028747!4d-147.8841552!16s%2Fg%2F11gdt_9dtp?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Little Raccoon Key: Jekyll Island, Georgia
  
  ![Interior of glamping tent with large bed at Little Raccoon Key.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-9162-d679-ad7f-b1e2edaf0000/12-little-raccoon-key.jpg?update-time=1755621519333&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Little Raccoon Key
  
  Little Raccoon Key – a small, uninhabited island accessible by a short boat ride from [Georgia](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-things-to-do-in-georgia)'s Jekyll Island – stands out from most other glamping destinations in the U.S. for one reason: There's just one campsite available. Not only will you have the entire reef island to yourself, but you'll be pampered by staff from start to finish. In addition to your private-island accommodations and the short boat tour there that often passes dolphins, you can request chef-prepared meals, pre-arrival grocery delivery and a lesson on oyster reefs around the island.
  
  Your campsite features most necessities, such as a luxury canvas tent, a memory foam mattress, a gas grill, a stove, a kettle, other cooking supplies, and an outdoor shower and toilet. You can also take advantage of a fire pit and barbecue area in the evening. While Little Raccoon Key provides a cooler for ice, it's recommended to bring your own so you can store several days' worth of food, since there's no refrigerator. Note that while Little Raccoon Key is pet-friendly, your dog might not be comfortable with the island's strong currents and rough terrain.
  
  Address: [1 Harbor Road, Suite No. 1, Jekyll Island, GA 31527](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Little+Raccoon+Key-Tours,+Charters,+and+Glamping/@31.0464139,-81.4239439,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x88e4dc18a4b27bf7:0x9093cf816367fc12!8m2!3d31.0464093!4d-81.421369!16s%2Fg%2F11d_wmfx7g?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Firelight Camps: Ithaca, New York
  
  ![Aerial view of Firelight Camps in the fall.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-917c-d679-ad7f-b1fc90940000/14-fall-tents-drone-by-sean-stalteri.jpg?update-time=1755621549678&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Sean Stalteri\|Courtesy of Firelight Camps
  
  Experience the natural beauty of upstate New York with a stay at Firelight Camps. This glamping site enjoys a scenic location in a wooded area that's only minutes away from local state parks as well as Ithaca's popular Collegetown neighborhood, making this particular destination easier to reach than most.
  
  Canvas drapes the natural wood beams of the tents, which come with either one king-size or two queen-size beds. Tents also feature hardwood floors, a private porch, rocking chairs, lanterns, and a desk and chair. Upgraded tents come with electricity, though it's important to note that none have private bathrooms; instead, there's a shared bathhouse with eco-friendly products.
  
  Guests can also expect to enjoy artisanal spirits at the on-site bar as well as a delicious and locally sourced breakfast each morning. Previous guests praise the comfortable beds as well as the resort staff's hospitality.
  
  Address: [1150 Danby Road, Ithaca, NY 14850](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Ithaca+by+Firelight+Camps/@42.4014455,-76.5074999,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x89d08058f6ca365d:0xca9c54e56c7d21d9!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d42.4014416!4d-76.504925!16s%2Fg%2F11b6337yl7?entry=ttu)
  
  Read:
  
  [18 Most Romantic Getaways in New York State](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-romantic-getaways-in-new-york-state)
  
  ## Sandy Pines Campground: Kennebunkport, Maine
  
  ![Interior of extravagant glamping tent at Sandy Pines Campground.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000173-917c-d679-ad7f-b1fc99a80000/courtesy-of-sandy-pines-campground-credit-douglas-merriam.jpg?update-time=1755621589941&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Douglas Merriam\|Courtesy of Sandy Pines Campground
  
  Kennebunkport is known for its beaches and quaint downtown area, which often leaves the nearby green spaces overlooked by visitors. But Sandy Pines Campground offers travelers the chance to experience these underrated landscapes in [Kennebunkport](https://travel.usnews.com/Kennebunkport_ME/Things_To_Do/) without sacrificing proximity to the water. Guests can choose from a variety of unique accommodation options, including cottages, A-frame huts and traditional glamping tents.
  
  The tents for couples are outfitted with a king-size bed, a seating area, a private deck, a minifridge, lighting, air conditioning and a small heater, and bath amenities. The family tent options have similar features but come with either a daybed in the main tent or a separate, smaller tent with twin beds.
  
  Guests can take advantage of glampground amenities such as shared bathhouses, a saltwater pool and lots of activities for kids, including craft sessions. You can also rent a kayak and paddleboard from the property, depending on the tides. Previous visitors say Sandy Pines Campground is especially ideal for families.
  
  Address: [277 Mills Road, Kennebunkport, ME 04046](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Sandy+Pines+Campground/@43.3983931,-70.4338439,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x4cb2a91941ed2b53:0xffa00c9de354047f!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d43.3983892!4d-70.431269!16s%2Fg%2F1th0xz07?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Mendocino Grove: Mendocino, California
  
  ![Glamping tents in Mendocino Grove.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000189-98c3-d382-a9ff-99ffcdf30000/group-of-glamping-tents-credit-mendocino-grove.jpg?update-time=1755621614642&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Mendocino Grove
  
  Find a serene glamping experience in one of [California's most breathtaking small towns](https://travel.usnews.com/gallery/beautiful-small-towns-in-california). Mendocino Grove sits within a forest bluff adjacent to the town, affording spectacular views of the camp's towering trees and the coast.
  
  Most glamping tents sleep two guests, but some sleep up to four or six. You'll also find some options that are dog-friendly. Beds vary in size and come with down comforters and wool blankets; the adult beds also feature heated mattress pads. All tents come equipped with fire pits, picnic tables and limited electricity for powering lamps (which have USB ports) as well as other approved devices, including CPAP machines. Private decks with leather butterfly chairs complete the glamping accommodations.
  
  Other on-site amenities include two shared bathhouses with organic products (plus a dog wash), hammocks, a bocce ball court and yoga. Enjoy complimentary coffee, tea and cocoa at The Meadow Commons, which also offers Wi-Fi and lends out books and games.
  
  Address: [9601 California state Route 1, Mendocino, CA 95460](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Mendocino+Grove/@39.2958854,-123.7980649,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x8081b2b371ae2641:0xe3430da0f313509b!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d39.2958813!4d-123.79549!16s%2Fg%2F1tfm1p8c?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Huttopia: Multiple Locations
  
  ![Interior of cabin at Huttopia.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-2502-dc34-a9f3-a75e97b50000/huttopia.jpg?update-time=1755621642897&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Huttopia
  
  What started as a small campsite in the French Alps has since expanded to more than 60 locations across three continents, including eight sites across the U.S. and Canada. Huttopia's goal is to provide travelers with comforts that go above traditional camping but aren't so comfortable that you'll stay in your tent rather than explore the beautiful surroundings of its properties.
  
  Huttopia's six types of glamping accommodations range from 215 square feet to 625 square feet, with some housing up to six guests. All tents and cabins offer plush beds and electricity, while some have private bathrooms, kitchenettes or kitchens, and decks. Shared bathhouses are available to guests who don't have private toilets and showers.
  
  Because Huttopia was established in France, you'll find French touches throughout the grounds, such as freshly made pastries at the on-site cafe and bistro area as well as good wine. Other camp amenities include outdoor swimming pools, a camp store and summer activities like live music, magic shows and fitness classes.
  
  ## AutoCamp: Multiple Locations
  
  ![Exterior shot of van and grounds at AutoCamp.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-2502-dc34-a9f3-a75e97800000/autocampfalmouthaug2020-50-credit-matt-kisiday.jpg?update-time=1755621670475&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Matt Kisiday\|Courtesy of AutoCamp
  
  If your idea of glamping is spending the night in an RV – but you don't have the budget or patience to buy one – it's time to explore AutoCamp. This glamping resort company specializes in Airstream accommodations, with seven locations (and counting) ranging from national parks to beaches. Airstream amenities vary slightly by location, but you can expect plush beds, a private bathroom with natural bath products, air conditioning, a kitchenette and a bright sitting room. The 31-foot Airstreams are also equipped with basic cookware and a grill. All locations offer traditional standalone glamping tents, and some accommodations are pet-friendly. You'll find accessible suites in several locations as well, including AutoCamp Yosemite and AutoCamp Cape Cod.
  
  Like the accommodations, some of the on-site programming varies by resort. For instance, AutoCamp Zion has a pool, and the Sequoia location offers river access. But all of AutoCamp's outposts are dog-friendly and offer complimentary cruiser bikes (first come, first served), Wi-Fi and coffee. They also promise on-site stores for provisions, including wine and beer.
  
  ## Lakedale Resort: San Juan Island, Washington
  
  ![Interior of glamping tent at Lakedale Resort in the evening.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-250a-dba3-abd7-273f1c930001/34-interior-lakedale.jpg?update-time=1755621712282&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Lakedale Resort
  
  Off the coast of Washington state, Lakedale offers glamping on San Juan Island, a picturesque place that can only be accessed by ferry or floatplane. Here, year-round glamping accommodations consist of yurts. (Log cabins and the lodge are also available year-round, but yurts truly encompass the glamping spirit.) Each comes with a king-size bed, a full-size sleeper sofa, an en suite bathroom, a wet bar, a minifridge, a flat-panel TV, seating indoors and outside, and a private deck with a hot tub and barbecues
  
  In the summer months, travelers also have the option to glamp in a canvas cabin or cottage, ideal for families with space for up to six guests. Complimentary on-site activities at Lakedale include lawn games, bike rentals and water sports on the resort's three spring-fed lakes.
  
  Address: [4313 Roche Harbor Road, Friday Harbor, San Juan Island, WA 98250](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Lakedale/@48.575757,-123.0828622,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x548f7cf9308617c5:0xf0e48930525cddda!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d48.5757535!4d-123.0802873!16s%2Fg%2F1wc47ntv?entry=ttu)
  
  Read:
  
  [The 11 Best Weekend Getaways From Seattle](https://travel.usnews.com/features/the-best-weekend-getaways-from-seattle)
  
  ## The Inn & Spa at Cedar Falls: Logan, Ohio
  
  ![Interior of a cabin with a kitchen at The Inn & Spa at Cedar Falls.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-250a-dba3-abd7-273f1d0c0000/35-kitchen-the-inn-spa-at-cedar-falls.jpg?update-time=1755621756622&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of The Inn & Spa at Cedar Falls
  
  Surrounded by the lush forests of Hocking Hills State Park in Ohio, the Inn & Spa at Cedar Falls is one of the [most romantic getaways in Ohio](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-romantic-getaways-in-ohio). Choose from fully equipped cabins and cottages (some of which are pet-friendly) as well as yurts and "geodomes." Each insulated yurt has a king bed or two twin beds, a full bathroom, a kitchenette that includes a gas log stove and microwave, a wood deck, and rocking chairs. The geodomes are a luxurious cross between a traditional suite and a tent. Each geodome comes outfitted with one king-size bed, and offers similar amenities to the yurts, plus a kitchen table and sofa. Both yurts and geodomes are available year-round.
  
  All guests have access to a full-service spa and a restaurant, lauded by guests for its food (which includes complimentary breakfast); both are located in 1840s-style log cabins. Of course, you'll also find outdoor activities galore, most notably exploring Hocking Hills State Park, one of the [top Ohio destinations](https://travel.usnews.com/features/top-things-to-do-in-ohio).
  
  Address: [21190 Ohio state Route 374, Logan, OH 43138](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Inn+%26+Spa+at+Cedar+Falls/@39.4249651,-82.5279149,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x8847ea8ee015e2d5:0x46d2d1cb38472566!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d39.424961!4d-82.52534!16s%2Fg%2F1tfg8c2s?entry=ttu)
  
  ## The Vintages Trailer Resort: Dayton, Oregon
  
  ![Interior shot of a bright trailer at The Vintages Trailer Resort.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000181-250a-dba3-abd7-273f1de70000/the-vintages.jpg?update-time=1755621779612&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of The Vintages Trailer Resort
  
  The Vintages Trailer Resort offers 34 trailers in a variety of styles, nine of which welcome dogs and all of which make the perfect home base for those exploring Oregon's Willamette Valley, otherwise known as Oregon wine country. Trailer styles and designs vary, but all offer comfortable beds, bathrooms – or at the very least toilets – air conditioning and heating, and outdoor grills. Separate shower facilities are also available. Pro tip: Book the 1956 Spartan Royal Mansion trailer in the warmer months to stargaze from an open-air soaker tub.
  
  The on-site amenities at The Vintages Trailer Resort are almost as good as the trailers themselves. Offerings include a seasonal swimming pool, fire pits, a general store and complimentary cruiser bikes for enjoying Dayton, the gateway to several local vineyards. Even better is the staff, whom previous guests praise in their glowing reviews of the resort.
  
  Address: [16205 SE Kreder Road, Dayton, OR 97114](https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Vintages+Trailer+Resort/@45.2273053,-123.0768712,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x549544291e87c535:0x81d8d0809dfe9701!8m2!3d45.2273016!4d-123.0742963!16s%2Fg%2F11btmrvjq2?entry=ttu)
  
  ## Black Tree Resort: Lake George, Colorado
  
  ![Exterior of glamping tent at Black Tree Resort at sunset.](https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000198-c2a2-de38-a7da-d7a3b1550000/credit-black-tree-resort.jpg?update-time=1755612097981&size=responsiveFlow640)
  
  Courtesy of Black Tree Resort
  
  The luxurious Black Tree Resort is located about 50 miles west of [Colorado Springs](https://travel.usnews.com/Colorado_Springs_CO/Things_To_Do/). Glamping tents here feature two queen-size beds, a wood-burning stove, handcrafted furniture and a dining table where Colorado cuisine is delivered for breakfast, lunch and dinner – all of which are included in the daily rate, along with nonalcoholic beverages. A private bathroom separate from the tent boasts Rocky Mountain Soap Market Toiletries and modern amenities.
  
  Outside each tent, guests can read a book on the cushioned seats under the covered patio, relax in Adirondack chairs around the private fire pit or enjoy a snack at the picnic table. You'll even have your own personal golf cart to drive around camp. Recent visitors rave about the food and recommend hiking on the many miles of nearby trails, especially in Eleven Mile State Park.
  
  Address: [8463 state Route 92, Lake George, CO 80827](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Black+Tree+Resort/@38.9601074,-105.4638304,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x876b352112954f8d:0x822c849f1abfa7e3!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d38.9601033!4d-105.4612555!16s%2Fg%2F11gwdztf4d?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDgwNC4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D)
  
  ## Wild Haven Sonoma: Healdsburg, California
  
  If you want a [Sonoma](https://travel.usnews.com/Sonoma_CA/Things_To_Do/) getaway that doesn't break the bank, consider glamping at Wild Haven Sonoma. You'll have several options for accommodation, including a 180-square-foot cabin that features a queen-size bed, skylights, a bistro patio and a fire pit. Families can upgrade to a cabin that includes a futon or a full loft for the kids. Guests can also stay in a dog-friendly furnished tent, some of which are riverside. The communal bathrooms for both cabins and tents include showers and changing rooms.
  
  There are plenty of amenities to enjoy around the Wild Haven glampground. With a stretch of private river access, swimming, kayaking, tubing or relaxing in a waterfront chair are all popular activities. Around the property, you'll also find a camp store, a covered cooking area with five barbecues, and classes and events like yoga and wine tasting.
  
  Address: [2411 Alexander Valley Road, Healdsburg, CA 95448](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Wildhaven+Sonoma+Glamping/@38.6584435,-122.8360386,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!3m8!1s0x80841161b641c4af:0xaa21c9e3232f29d5!5m2!4m1!1i2!8m2!3d38.6584393!4d-122.8334637!16s%2Fg%2F11j94kqwzy?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDgwNC4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D)
  
